      "title": "Sri Lanka expecting two crude oil cargos this month: Minister",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A crude oil cargo of 100,000 metric tons is scheduled to arrive in Sri Lanka later tonight (Aug 13) and will undergo quality sampling tomorrow, Minister of Power & Energy Kanchana Wijesekera says.",
        "Meanwhile, another crude oil cargo of 120,000 metric tons is expected to reach Colombo between August 23 and 29, he said further in a tweet.",
        "Both cargos are Russia\u2019s Urals crude oil, the lawmaker added."
      ],
